    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n8390" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">Σκαιαί</span></b> : <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πύλαι</span>, and without <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πύλαι</span>,
            <i><span class="en">Il. 3.263</span></i>; the <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">Scaean</span>
          Gate of Troy, the only gate of the city which Homer mentions by name.
          It appears to have faced the Greek camp, affording a view over the
          Trojan plain, <i><span class="en">Il. 3.145</span></i>, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">149, 263,</span>
